{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/visualizing-episodic-memory-with-hopfield-network-a6e8bde967cb", "time": 1683008944.945411, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/visualizing-episodic-memory-with-hopfield-network-a6e8bde967cb/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Visualizing Episodic Memory with Hopfield Network | by Muhammad Abduh | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Visualizing Episodic Memory with Hopfield Network", "description": "In 2018, I wrote an article describing the neural model and its relation to artificial neural networks. One chapter of the book that I refer to explains that certain properties could emerge when a\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/a-history-of-triggering-artificial-neuron-d1d9853d9fdc", "anchor_text": "article", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.amazon.com/Fundamentals-Computational-Neuroscience-Thomas-Trappenberg/dp/0199568413", "anchor_text": "book", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.researchgate.net/publication/16246447_Neural_Networks_and_Physical_Systems_with_Emergent_Collective_Computational_Abilities", "anchor_text": "Hopfield Network", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0301008206000360", "anchor_text": "Cutsuridis, V. & Wennekers, T", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://www.amazon.com/Organization-Behavior-Neuropsychological-Theory/dp/0805843000", "anchor_text": "Hebb, D.O. 1949", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://github.com/mabdh/hopfield-network", "anchor_text": "source code", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://hopfield-network.mabdh.now.sh/", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://reinforcement-learning-q-learning.mabdh.now.sh/", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 7}], "all_paragraphs": ["In 2018, I wrote an article describing the neural model and its relation to artificial neural networks. One chapter of the book that I refer to explains that certain properties could emerge when a set of neurons work together and form a network. A lot of theories are there in the book, but what attracts me more is a network that can simulate how human memory works called Hopfield Network [Hopfield, J.J. 1982].", "Hopfield Network is the predecessor of Restricted Boltzmann Machine (RBM) and Multilayer Perceptron (MLP). It is an energy-based auto-associative memory, recurrent, and biologically inspired network.", "It has been shown behaviorally that the CA3 supports spatial rapid one-trial learning, learning of arbitrary associations where space is a component, pattern completion, spatial short-term memory, and sequence learning by associations formed between successive items. [Cutsuridis, V. & Wennekers, T. 2006]", "Different with other neural networks that use backpropagation to learn the weight, Hopfield Network uses Hebb\u2019s learning or Hebbian Learning [Hebb, D.O. 1949] which is also a biologically-inspired learning. The idea behind Hebbian Learning is the connection between two neurons (synapse) will be stronger if the neurons at both ends are actively correlated. In Hopfield Network, neurons only have two states, activated and non-activated. Sometimes people quantified the activated state with 1 and non-activated state with 0. Sometimes they also quantified the activated state with 1 and non-activated state with -1.", "At the end of 2019, I spared my time tried to simulate and visualize how the memory recall with Hopfield Network works. The simulation and visualization that I made is a web application so it is accessible and can be tried by all people. There are a lot of explanation about Hopfield Network out there and it will be redundant (or not?) if I also explained that here. Instead, I am opening this source code of the web app for people to explore and get the idea of the implementation. The link is here.", "The image above shows the screenshot of the web app to visualize Hopfield Network. There are two sections, Train and Predict. You can draw some patterns (3 at the most) on each of the grid or could also choose the predefined patterns provided. After the pattern is drawn, you can click the Train 3 Patterns button. When it is done,t the network already memorized the 3 patterns provided above. You can try to visualize how Hopfield Network recall one pattern by drawing the (incomplete) pattern in the Predict grid. Below is the GIF when we play around with the visualization.", "This article and simulation hopefully enlightens some people who is still puzzled with how a Hopfield Network works. It might also be useful for people who learn something better visually.", "Beside Hopfield Network, I also create a web app to simulate how Q-learning works. Q-learning is one of reinforcement learning algorithm. You can check that here.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fa6e8bde967cb&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fvisualizing-episodic-memory-with-hopfield-network-a6e8bde967cb&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fvisualizing-episodic-memory-with-hopfield-network-a6e8bde967cb&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav------------------